==English==

===Etymology===
From {{m|en|total}}, the reduplicated ''tee'' being an intensifier – “T-total”, 1830s.

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# [[abstinent|Abstinent]] from [[alcohol]]; never [[drink]]ing [[alcohol]].
#: {{syn|en|on the wagon|straightedge}}
#: {{ant|en|alcoholic|dipsomaniac|drunkard}}
# Opposed to the drinking of alcohol.
# {{lb|en|dated|emphatic}} [[total|Total]].
#* '''1858''', Samuel Putnam Avery, ''The Harp of a Thousand Strings: Or, Laughter for a Lifetime'' (page 331)
#*: That's a '''teetotal''' lie.

